#. +> trunk6
#: ImportExport/Export.cpp:184
#, kde-format
msgid ""
"<p>With this option you may limit the maximum dimensions (width and height) "
"of your images. Doing so will make the resulting export file smaller, but "
"will of course also make the quality worse if someone wants to see the "
"exported images with larger dimensions.</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>このオプションによって画像の最大寸法 (幅と高さ) を制限することができます。"
"有効にするとエクスポートしたファイルのサイズは小さくなりますが、エクスポート"
"された画像を高解像度で見ると当然のことながら画質が悪くなります。</p>"

#. +> trunk6
#: ImportExport/Export.cpp:191
#, fuzzy, kde-format
#| msgid ""
#| "<p>When exporting images, bear in mind that there are two things the "
#| "person importing these images again will need:<br>1) meta information "
#| "(image content, date etc.)<br>2) the images themselves.</p><p>The images "
#| "themselves can either be placed next to the .kim file, or copied into "
#| "the .kim file. Copying the images into the .kim file works well for a "
#| "recipient who wants all, or most of those images, for example when "
#| "emailing a whole group of images. However, when you place the images on "
#| "the Web, a lot of people will see them but most likely only download a "
#| "few of them. It works better in this kind of case, to separate the images "
#| "and the .kim file, by place them next to each other, so the user can "
#| "access the images s/he wants.</p>"
msgid ""
"<p>When exporting images, bear in mind that there are two things the person "
"importing these images again will need:<br/>1) meta information (image "
"content, date etc.)<br/>2) the images themselves.</p><p>The images "
"themselves can either be placed next to the .kim file, or copied into "
"the .kim file. Copying the images into the .kim file works well for a "
"recipient who wants all, or most of those images, for example when emailing "
"a whole group of images. However, when you place the images on the Web, a "
"lot of people will see them but most likely only download a few of them. It "
"works better in this kind of case, to separate the images and the .kim file, "
"by place them next to each other, so the user can access the images s/he "
"wants.</p>"
msgstr ""
"<p>画像をエクスポートするときは、その画像をインポートする人が必要とするものが"
"二つあることに留意してください。<br/>1) メタ情報 (画像の内容、日付など)<br/"
">2) 画像自体<p><p>画像自体は .kim ファイルの隣に置くか、.kim ファイルの中にコ"
"ピーするかのいずれかを選択できます。すべてまたは大部分の画像を見たい人が受け"
"取る場合 (一連の画像をまとめてメールで送るときなど)、画像を .kim ファイルにコ"
"ピーするといいでしょう。しかし、画像をウェブ上に置くときは、見る人はたくさん"
"いてもダウンロードされるのはおそらく一部の画像だけです。そのような場合は、"
"ユーザが見たい画像にアクセスできるように、画像を .kim ファイルの隣に置いて両"
"者を分離した方がいいでしょう。</p>"

